# Template Analysis and Selection

## Comparison of GitHub Project Templates

| Template         | Columns / Workflow                | Automation Features                            | Agile Suitability                                          |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| Basic Kanban     | To Do, In Progress, Done          | No automation                                  | Suitable for simple workflows but lacks advanced features  |
| Automated Kanban | To Do, In Progress, Done          | Automatically moves issues when status changes | Highly suitable for Agile due to automation and efficiency |
| Bug Triage       | New, Investigating, Fixed         | Auto-labeling bugs                             | Suitable for maintenance but not full development          |
| Team Planning    | Backlog, Ready, In Progress, Done | Supports planning and prioritization           | Suitable for larger teams and structured Agile planning    |



## Selected Template: Automated Kanban

The **Automated Kanban** template was selected for this project because it aligns well with Agile principles and supports efficient workflow management.

### Justification

* Automation reduces manual work by automatically moving issues across columns.
* Supports continuous delivery by tracking task progress in real time.
* Integrates well with GitHub Issues created in Assignment 6.
* Enhances productivity by ensuring tasks move smoothly through development stages.

This makes it ideal for managing the Assignment Tracker System, where tasks such as user stories need to be tracked from creation to completion.
